</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
The melanic (black) form (♂) and a nearly black form, with obscure reddish patches on abdominal terga 2-4 (♀), are known from Norway (near Hovet and near Geitryggtunnelen, leg. E. Heibo, CEH), and the melanic form also from Kamtschatka, Russia (a syntype female of 
<taxonomicName family="Tenthredinidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. pratensis subsp. var. var. totus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="variety" species="pratensis" subSpecies="var." variety="totus">D. pratensis var. totus</taxonomicName>
determined by R. Malaise, in NHRS, see also under 
<taxonomicName family="Tenthredinidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. yukonensis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="yukonensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">D. yukonensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
